Serves 2-4Ingredients:1 litre water1 vegetable stock cube2 slices dried galangal2 fresh red chillies, sliced125ml ( cup) chopped fresh coriander1 stalk lemon grass, sliced100g mushroom stems, cut julienne style300g shelled and deveined prawnsJuice of 1 lemonMethod:1) Pour the water into a deep saucepan, add the stock cube and bring to a boil.2) Add galangal and cook on moderate heat for 10 minutes. Add chillies, coriander, lemon grass and mushrooms, and cook for a further 10 minutes.3) Stir in prawns with lemon juice. Turn up heat to boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and serve.